deleted: Various commentators and scholars have offered diverse opinions regarding Obama's foreign policy, often focusing on what is referred to as Obama's doctrine. Among these perspectives, some critics argue that the new US foreign policy under Obama was perceived as excessively lenient towards the country's adversaries, leading to concerns about the unequivocal support for US allies being compromised.<ref>[https://blogs.timesofisrael.com/u-s-foreign-policy-in-whirlfall/ Vitenberg, Dan (22 November 2013) "U.S. Foreign Policy in ‘Whirlfall’", The Times of Israel]</ref>
